  "text": "A study evaluated PCR in urine from patients with highlevel antigenuria in the second-generation Histoplasma antigen LDT observed low sensitivity. [CITATION_1] Urine was cultured for Histoplasma at MiraVista Diagnostics and stored at −80°C for PCR testing. Five of the 51 specimens grew Histoplasma and the PCR was positive in four yielding a sensitivity of 7.8% (4 of 51). The antigen concentration was above the upper limit of the assay in those five specimens.",
